Slow merchant. Had to wait outside for 15 min just to get in. Careless employees

The absolute worst service since covid. I ordered separate items on the menu, When I received my order they where all in the same container. Mind you they where for different people. I couldn’t tell who’s food was who’s. Along with a person who’s working not understanding any of the things I was trying to explain. Just an overall horrible experience when I heard great things 😤
Great place, very affordable. Have handled covid really well!

Eat here often on Uber—it’s amazing and delicious. Good portion size too. I would recommend the combo sushi... you get three rolls for the price of one. Spider roll is also awesome—not as big portions but delicious and crunchy
Ate here 2-3 times. They were a little bit slow to the order. Sushi was not as good as other places I've had in DC and was not cheap either. I would recommend another place.

This place is my favorite sushi spot in the city. Consistently, everything is FRESH and great quality. I’ve eaten here about 10 times and not had a bad food experience once. Always delicious, always presented well, always consistent flavor and taste.  I will say, in terms of customer service, that the staff can be a little...short tempered when you go to order, but for the quality of the food, this is easily overlooked. Id recommend looking at the menu in advance.  I’d also recommend getting sushi there, though there are many equally delicious options available (pad Thai, sweet and sour chicken, many others)  because it’s one of the better sushi spots in the city. Spicy maki combo platter is my go-to.
I’ve only done takeout but it was quick and contactless. Sushi was fresh. They have good prices for their sushi rolls and their combos are a great deal!
Favorite place for sushi

My chirashi bowl had a flower in it. Everything was delicious and fresh. It had white rice, shrimp, tuna, salmon among other fish sashimi I wasnt sure exactly what it was but it was delicious. Everything came fast the service was good. This bowl was a decent size for 16 but its also one of the pricier things on the menu. I recommend it to anyone

Nice little affordable cafe for sushi and other Asian food.  They're quite generous with the amount of fish they put in their sushi rolls, so if you like that it's perfect, but if you don't, maybe order some extra rice.
Fantastic spot for great fast-Asian food. They got Thai, Korean, Chinese and  Japanese. If you're hungry and feeling the Adian Persuasion, check this spot out (Beer served(
Love the variety of sushi and they have a great menu
I didnt get the new dish I wanted to try, the pork belly with egg noodles, but the beef chow fun was very tasty! The passionfruit tea was very passionfruit-y too.  You should try it!

This place is nothing fancy, but I often pop into the Sushi Bar for fast, fresh sushi. They are already super cheap, but their sushi lunch specials are a major steal. They are also very quick when doing delivery or take out- my food is always ready early.  Insider Tip: Their shrimp tempura rolls come with avocado in them!
Good for sushi rolls.

Horrible place. Orde here from Postmates.  They forgot about my chiashi.  Tell me they forgot to pack it.  I told them that’s fine and can they deliver to me.  It is only about a mile.  They told me no and I have to go there to pick up or go though Postmates again and pay deliver fee again for their mistake.   I told them I don’t have a car at dc, and they just said can’t deliver to me.
I always get the Spicy Maki Combo off the sushi menu.
I already had low expectations for the food from this restaurant. I was surprised when it turned out to be even worse than what I expected. Panda Express makes better Chinese food than this.
Love the sushi
Buba tea is amazing
Good food and good service
(Translated by Google) It's so delicious!  (Original) 太好吃啦！

I placed a take out order and the person that took my order forgot about me claiming she didn't see me waiting, so I sat there close to thirty minutes. Keep in mind there were only three people in the restaurant dining, so instead of walking around the counter or simply calling out that the order was ready they just went about their business like I was never there. I have been to this establishment at least four times and they usually bring the order to the customer. There is no excuse for such poor service.
Good fresh food. Good prices. Near the subway and across from Giant foods. If you eat in you can get drink refills.
The lunch Sushi rolls special works for me. Pan Asian joint. Tasty, reasonably priced, and quite.

Sushi was really good. However, the person working the cash register and taking orders was very short and rude. Her poor attitude was a HUGE distraction and disappointment. Her attitude/behaviour means we will never return here to spend our money.
I never stopped in to this restaurant.

Just step up my workout to three days a week. Weight training and swimming. My SUMMER BODY is here! Two more weeks i am putting my 6 pack on social media 😄! Great place with good staff and community folks.

The after taste of vinegar threw me off i love pad thai but this isn't it at all and my sticky rice with mango missed the mark as well the menu has a variety of dishes im willing to try but this will not be one of them  This was supposed to be a smoothie looks more like slushy yuck
Very slow service but food is always fresh!

It feels like they never clean the tables so it's always sticky but even still it's one of my fave spots for Asian cuisine. If I'm in a rush I'll order sushi rolls to go but if I have time I'm definitely going for the salmon Bento box! It's about a block away from Columbia Heights Metro Station so it's extremely convenient.
Pretty affordable asian food. Pad see ew is my favorite here
They have a huge menu with nothing particularly outstanding. Doesn't help that these guys just keep getting my orders wrong.

Shanghai Tokyo has become my favorite spot for Asian cuisine in Columbia Heights. Available on GrubHub and UberEats as well as carry out or dine in, Shanghai Tokyo has a wide variety of entrees from many Asian cultures. They take time to prepare the food, so expect a 15 minute wait, but it's worth it. My favorite dishes there are the teriyaki bento boxes and the drunken noodles. Try them!

ordered on uber eats, and got miso soup which was bland and barely had any tofu or greens in it, shrimp Shumai that barely had any meat in it and strawberry milk tea which I had such high expectations for but it just tasted artificial and powder-Ish. Last time I came in to order pad Thai (my favorite food) and it wasn’t really good... so now I feel like I don’t wanna eat pad Thai from anywhere again just cause of this one experience. Was so excited to have a diverse asian spot near me but very disappointed about the taste of everything. Crab salad was the only thing that was alright but honestly how do you make a bad crab salad? Lol
Good food. Reasonably priced. Fountain drink selection was limited. Several flavors were unavailable.
Two nights ago, I ordered from here for the first time. I decided to try the Shrimp Pad Thai & the Mexican Roll....SO GOOD 🙌🏿 Highly recommend this place.
We came here for lunch and had the sushi special. The sushi was the worst I ever had! If you want cheap sushi, get the one from HT.
Food it's really good I always visit this place on Wednesdays. the owners are really friendly , always looks clean .

This was my first time coming to this particular resturaunt. Prior to coming in I placed my order ahead of time. When I walked I stood by the register and about 3 different workers seen me standing there. Not once was I greeted upon waiting there or asked if I had or wanted to place a order. 4 different customers had gotten taken care of before me and had been spoken to. After waiting for so long I asked the lady behind the counter is this where I stand for pick up and she ignored me. What makes it even worse is that my order was behind the register the whole time I was there and it was not crowded at all. I think the employees should really work on they're customer service. I will not be ordering from here anymore.

Ordered 2 smoothies. One mango and one passion fruit. I don't recommend the passion fruit.  The man taking our order (pictured at cash register) was very short and unfriendly when we were asking him questions. He seemed like he was in a hurry to nowhere. I understand they must've been busy with deliveries, because there was only 1 person in front of us, but that shouldn't compromise customer service and how you treat people.
Delicious green curry with veggies and tofu. Metal utensils (not plastic) and stone dishware.
Love the food!

Ordered online for pick up. Got there there and they charged me an additional $5 on top of my order and said there prices online was wrong. I've been going here since I moved to DC but that don't matter so....
Clean quick service good staff and good customer services
Great Asian fusion in DC
Delicious food, nice interior and quick carryout service.

I love Shanghai Tokyo cafe. Their food is super fresh and delicious. It is well made and the employees are attentive and friendly. Sushi options are great. Major plus that they are opened until 10:30pm during the weekday.
We enjoyed the food but the staff is not too communicated.
Great food, location and prices.
Consistent pan-Asian food. A convenient takeout option.
The food is really good, it is not very expensive and you get a good portion for the price. The sushi is really good and they have soy paper!! Next time in DC, we will go eat here again!

My favorite quick and delicious go-to asian restaurant. Love their teriyaki tofu meal and their salmon lovers sushi. Love their soups and salads and their pan fried veggie dumplings. Great quality food, great service, and usually pretty quick.

Used to be good but stopped prioritizing in store customers and started prioritizing the delivery services who's drivers are mean and pushy to customers. They don't give accurate times for the order to be done told me 20 minutes ended up taking an hour and they still charged us full price they also missed items in the order. When I called back they said I was wrong.  Avoid if you don't want to waste your time and have your intelligence insulted
Sushi that gives you the most for your buck. Great lunch deals and the quantity is more than at most DC sushi places for an equal or lesser price. Favorite sushi spot.
Great neighborhood Chinese spot. Fast and friendly.
Fast casual type restaurant with a huge selection of asian foods, everything I've ordered has been satisfactory
Good Asian fusion food & sushi
Casual place with carry-out vibes, but there's plenty of seating and the food is actually really good and the prices are reasonable.

This place was amazing! I walked in during lunch one day and grabbed me a shrimp and broccoli lunch special. The staff was nice. The lemonade iced tea was on point and everything went smoothly. The second time i came (within the week)i had ordered the genereal tsos shrimp and sushi. My partner ordered the shrimp Pad Thai. Food Was hot and they provide great containers for you to take home your leftovers in. Jenny was really sweet! They also have the best fried rice I ever had in my life. Which was crazy....and the leftovers reheat well. If your ever in town and your tired of old heat lamp panda express or getting carried at some of these carryouts stop by. The sushi specials are awesome and the atmosphere was welcoming. Its one of my favorite spots now. Hopefully you'll give it a try and it will  be one of yours.
Its average Chinese/Asian fast dining.
Definitely recommend! I got the Salmon Lovers, which comes with a salad or miso soup. Quaint small space, nothing extravagant but it's clean and the staff is friendly. And they have a fish tank.
Delicious food.
Good selection and nice consistency of American Chinese food
Understaff, slow service, and our orders were mixed up! The server doesn't have any clue on who's food belongs to.. I'm not coming back that's for sure!!!! 👎👎👎👎👎

Wonderful place for those seeking a bargain. The service is fantastic and the food is a steal compared to some of the pricier places around town. While the sushi doesn't compare to somewhere like sushi taro, the menu variety and prices are enough to keep me coming back at least once or twice a week. Can't recommend it enough.

Honestly, I'm not crazy about the food at all. The pad thai lacks flavour completely and super spicey. But the lady was so nice to remake it, even though I should have read the menu, I've just never had it served spicy. Canned pineapple in the fried rice and not the mango in the mango sticky rice should be seasonable, yukky with unripe mango. Otherwise it is clean and very friendly people.
Everything I've had there taste good
Great food, great staff, if you want a place where there is little to know noise or no crowd great place as long as you don't take my seat!
The food is great and it comes out steaming hot. I love it!! I reccomend the general tsao chicken
Sichuan chicken was average at best.
Love this place for great and consistent Chinese, sushi rolls w fresh fish and Thai.
Quality of food went down. Chicken is fatty and bad quality.
Wide variety of pan Asian foods. Have only tried a few but overall of much higher quality than similarly priced takeout spots in the area.
(Translated by Google) Good Asian meal, good ingredients and affordable.  (Original) 不错的亚洲餐，食材好，实惠。
I thought the food was really good, sushi and Chinese dishes. The chicken teriyaki was delicious.

They offer Chinese, Sushi, and some Thai foods. The food is good and offers a nice variety as there aren't many restaurants with these options in Columbia Heights. I've only gotten take out, but be sure to call ahead or you could be waiting for over a half hour and check your order before leaving. They have messed up more than a couple times and it certainly doesn't build confidence. I would still go here, but when you have to double check every time if it's correct you might want to try Thip Khao or Mayflower.

So incredibly rude on the phone when calling for pickup or delivery ( have done both ) it leaves a dread even dealing with these people.  Absolutely horrible service from front of the house ( including cashiers at pickup )  for just mediocre sushi. Not worth the treatment which makes me feel sketch about the food itself. There are plenty of nearby competitors who will now have their business instead.
Volcano II Rolls ......speechless
We stumbled across this place looking for Panda Express and this place really took us for surprise! It was amazing! Vegetable Fried Rice was incredible!
Better than expected sushi and typical americanized pan-asian fare.
Decent chinese, thai, and japanese dishes. It's one level above a carry-out chinese place and one level below a sit down asian restaurant.
To be honest I've only ever had the sesame chicken and egg roll, but I get it on the regular. Best Chinese food in Columbia Heights

I love this place-- super convenient, quick, cheap, and delicious! Granted, I've only had the chicken pad Thai,  the drunken noodles, and a veggie sushi roll, but the quality and taste of those dishes probably speaks to the others.. The pad thai is better than any I've ever gotten in DC- lots of chicken, fried thin tofu, good spice and good amount of scallions, bean sprouts, and peanuts to top it off. And only $9! The drunken noodles are also very yummy but as a pad Thai enthusiast, it wins. Sushi is very fresh, made right there and they have the good ginger. Such a good addition to the fast food selection in Columbia Heights :)
Excellent food welcome to Columbia Hieghts
A beautiful and clean restaurant with fair prices and delicious food worth every minute to stay and eat.i hop they start putting Anime related things to attract more attention pls make it happen!=D

Just had lunch at this awesome spot. So glad you are here in the neighborhood! Had the spicy salmon with crunch roll, the philly roll and the chicken tempura roll with Miso soup. The staff were incredibly pleasant and the atmosphere is very welcoming. I'll be seeing you again very soon!
Food, staff, and selection make it the place to eat!

The staff is incredibly friendly and accommodating, the menu is extensive and runs the gamut of Panasian cuisine (including rice bowls and sushi), and the interior is clean, modern and comfortable -- really just delightful place to eat lunch. I had a bento box with chicken teriyaki, California rolls, a small salad, fried pork shumai and rice which was filling, well-priced and delicious.  My vegan partner was able to get a dish made without fish/oyster sauce that she enjoyed, though she wished they had more veggies and less tofu, but other dishes might have a better ratio.

My girlfriend and I came here for the first time tonight. I got Pad Thai and she got sushi. She was surprised to find she was full by the end- and she doesn't fill easily! I was taken aback by the spiciness of my meal, but they did warn me with the flame symbols on the menu, so now I respect the flame symbol. My girlfriend and I WILL be back!

Glad that a place for good, quick Asian food has moved into Columbia Heights! Salmon sushi tasted fresh with generous portions, the Kung Pao chicken far exceeded expectations, and the fried noodles were also good. Came in soon before closing on a weeknight and still had friendly, quick service. Will definitely be returning.
Try the cool new place you like it
